I am beyond impressed with this knife set! From the moment I opened the box, I could tell this was a high-quality product. The knives are beautifully crafted with a sleek, modern design that looks great on my kitchen counter. But more importantly ‚Äî they perform exceptionally well.Each knife is razor-sharp right out of the box and slices through meats, veggies, and bread effortlessly. I especially love the chef‚Äôs knife ‚Äî it‚Äôs perfectly balanced and feels great in the hand, making prep work a breeze. The handles are ergonomic and comfortable, even during longer cooking sessions.The set includes all the essentials, and the storage block keeps everything organized and within reach. I've noticed no dulling after weeks of daily use, and they're super easy to clean too.If you're looking for a dependable, stylish, and professional-quality knife set without breaking the bank, this is the one. I highly recommend it to home cooks and pros alike. You won‚Äôt be disappointed!

I recently upgraded from a basic budget knife set, and the Chicago Cutlery Malden collection has been a huge step up. Right out of the box, the quality is obvious. The stainless steel knives look sleek and modern, and the wooden block adds a warm, professional touch that fits perfectly with my kitchen d√©cor. It looks clean and stylish without being too flashy.The knives are well-balanced and feel solid in the hand. I really like the contoured handles‚Äîthey‚Äôre comfortable to grip and make prep work feel easier and smoother. So far, they‚Äôve cut everything with ease, from slicing vegetables to trimming meats. I also love the built-in sharpener in the block. It‚Äôs such a smart, space-saving feature that helps keep the blades sharp without needing to buy a separate tool.That said, I ran into one big issue. I accidentally left one of the knives in the sink overnight, and by morning it had rusted significantly. Not only did the blade rust, but it also left a large rust stain in my sink. That was really disappointing, especially since I assumed stainless steel would be more resistant. I now make sure to dry each knife immediately after washing and never leave them wet or in the sink.Overall, this set has been a great upgrade in terms of both looks and performance. Just be cautious about keeping them dry‚Äîthese definitely require some care. Still, for the price and functionality, I‚Äôd recommend them if you‚Äôre looking for a solid, attractive knife set.

column6: I stumbled across these knives while on vacation when the AirBnB we were staying at had a set in the kitchen.  I liked them so much that I looked them up and ordered a set for myself as soon as I came home.  That was in March 2019.They felt great in hand and actually made cooking more enjoyable because they performed so well.  We have used them almost daily for the past 7 years and have been BRUTAL on them.  They‚Äôve been dropped; left soaking in liquids for long periods of time; thrown around in the sink; smashed with heavy pans while in the sink; ran through the dishwasher a million times; etc. They have never been sharpened and are only slightly less sharp than when we first purchased them.  They are still very usable.The attached photos show the wear and tear as of today (1/8/26), nearly 7 years after purchase - both front and back. The purple chef‚Äôs knife is the most used knife in the kitchen, hands down.  While there has been definite wearing of the coating within the last year or two, the handles still look like the day I bought them.  Everything is tight and there is zero rust (even after sitting in the dishwasher or water for long periods).  Tips are still in tact.  You can‚Äôt possibly ask for better performance from a set of $30 knives.  These have outperformed more expensive knives I‚Äôve owned by a mile!I‚Äôve purchased multiple sets as gifts and I‚Äôm about to purchase a second set for a new home but my originals 100% still get the job done.  I couldn‚Äôt be happier with the quality of these knives.
Love the selection of knives in this set. I love that they have blade guards. They are the best set of knives I've ever owned.

This Cuisinart Graphix 8" Chef‚Äôs Knife has quickly become my go-to in the kitchen. The stainless steel blade is very sharp right out of the box and makes quick work of vegetables, meats, and herbs. Overall, I‚Äôm quite happy with this knife set. I like that it offers an excellent value for the price and has been a fantastic, affordable addition to my kitchen. The color coding is a wonderful feature that not only looks fun, but also helps prevent cross-contamination while cooking. Each knife is lightweight and easy to handle, making food preparation much more efficient. I particularly appreciate the varying sizes and shapes of the knives, which accommodate a range of cutting tracks, from slicing vegetables to carving meat. The blades are sharp and have held their edge relatively well, though I do find that they require regular honing to maintain their performance. The handles are comfortable, but I wish they had a bit more grip for added safety., especially when cutting tougher ingredients. The only reason I didn‚Äôt give it a full five stars is that I would have preferred a more durable material for the blades. They are good for everyday use,. But I‚Äôm concerned about longevity with high-volume cooking. These offer an affordable price and is perfect for home cooks. If you do decide to get these, be prepared to hone them and do not expect too much and just keep in mind the price paid for these.

The (6) 4.5 inch steak knives do not have a tang that reaches the back of the handle. The tang only goes about an inch or so into the handles. This causes the plastic handles to crack over time and eventually the blade breaks through the handle. The rest of the larger kitchen knives work fine, but the steak knives are cheaply made and will eventually break.
